README.md

# JANGO Bot - Automated Crypto Trading Bot

JANGO Bot is a **high-frequency automated trading bot** with **real-time market analysis, liquidity tracking, and AI-powered trading strategies**. It supports **Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain (BSC), and Solana**, featuring **auto-buy/sell, rug-pull detection, stop-loss, take-profit, and Telegram/Discord alerts** for secure and efficient trading.

## 🚀 Features

### 🏦 **Trading & Automation**

- ✅ **Auto-Buy & Auto-Sell** (Instant execution with gas optimization)
- ✅ **Sniping Bot** (Fast token purchases on new listings)
- ✅ **Stop-Loss & Take-Profit Automation** (Smart trading strategies)
- ✅ **Liquidity Tracking & Rug-Pull Detection** (Auto-sell if a scam is detected)
- ✅ **Multi-Chain Support** (Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, Solana)

### 🔒 **Security & Wallet Management**

- ✅ **Secure API & Private Key Encryption**
- ✅ **Multi-Wallet Support**
- ✅ **Prevents Buying Scam Tokens**
- ✅ **Telegram & Discord Alerts** (Trade notifications & market updates)

### 📊 **Trading Modes**

- 🎮 **Demo Mode**: Simulated trading (no real funds used)
- 🚀 **Live Trading Mode**: Executes real trades on the blockchain

## 📌 Installation & Setup

### **1️⃣ Clone the Repository**

```bash
 git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
 cd jango-bot
```

### **2️⃣ Install Dependencies**

```bash
npm install
```

### **3️⃣ Configure Environment Variables**

Create a `.env` file in the root directory and add the following:

```env
API_KEY=your-api-key
PRIVATE_KEY=your-private-wallet-key
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-telegram-bot-token
```

### **4️⃣ Start the Bot**

- **Demo Mode:**

```bash
node jango.js --demo
```

- **Live Trading Mode:**

```bash
node jango.js --live
```

## 🛠 Deployment (PM2 for Continuous Running)

To keep the bot running on a server:

```bash
pm install -g pm2
pm2 start jango.js --name jango-bot -- --live
pm2 save
pm2 startup
```

## 🖥 Web Interface (Frontend)

If you are using the frontend interface:

```bash
cd jango-front
npm install
npm start
```

## 🔗 API Endpoints

JANGO Bot provides REST API endpoints for automation:

```http
GET /api/trades  # Fetch trade history
POST /api/buy  # Execute a buy order
POST /api/sell  # Execute a sell order
```

## 🛡 Security Considerations

- **Use a secure VPS or dedicated machine** for deployment.
- **Never expose your private keys** in public repositories.
- **Enable firewall rules** to protect your API endpoints.

